OL,3,CJust Stop Oil activists convicted over
OL,4,Cprotest at World Snooker Championships
OL,6,FAsked about the impact of her actions
OL,7,Fon the people who had paid to watch a
OL,8,Fsnooker match, the defendant said:
OL,9,F"I'm really sorry about that but I was
OL,10,Freally aware that these same
OL,11,Findividuals would be so much worse
OL,12,Faffected by the impact of fossil
OL,13,Ffuels."
OL,15,FJudge Curtis said he had to consider
OL,16,Fthe defendants' rights under Article
OL,17,F10 -freedom of expression - and
OL,18,FArticle 11 - freedom of assembly and
OL,19,Fassociation - of the Human Rights Act
OL,20,Fbut he stressed this did not provide
OL,21,F"blanket immunity".
